  version: {fileID: 11400000, guid: d0ec49142d5c7c24fb05ee739840cab0, type: 2}
  description: 
  chapters:
  - verses:
    - name: '1: GreetingTrials, Testing, and Faith'
      title: GreetingTrials, Testing, and Faith
      number: 1
      content: ' James, a slave of God and of the Lord Jesus Christ, to the twelve
        tribes in the dispersion. Greetings! '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'Consider it all joy, my brothers, whenever you encounter various
        trials, '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'because you know that the testing of your faith produces endurance. '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'And let endurance have its perfect effect, so that you may be mature
        and complete, lacking in nothing. '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'Now if any of you lacks wisdom, let him ask for it from God, who
        gives to all without reservation and not reproaching, and it will be given
        to him. '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'But let him ask for it in faith, without any doubting, for the one
        who doubts is like the surf of the sea, driven by the wind and tossed about. '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'For that person must not suppose that he will receive anything from
        the Lord; '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'he is a double-minded man, unstable in all his ways. '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'Now let the brother of humble circumstances boast in his high position, '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'but the rich person in his humiliation, because he will pass away
        like a flower of the grass. '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'For the sun rises with its burning heat and dries up the grass, and
        its flower falls off, and the beauty of its appearance is lost. So also the
        rich person in his pursuits will wither away. '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'Blessed is the person who endures testing, because when he is approved
        he will receive the crown of life that he has promised to those who love
        him. '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "No one who is being tempted should say, \u201CI am being tempted
        by God,\u201D for God cannot be tempted by evil, and he himself tempts no
        one. "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'But each one is tempted when he is dragged away and enticed by his
        own desires. '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'Then desire, after it has conceived, gives birth to sin, and sin,
        when it is brought to completion, gives birth to death. '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'Do not be deceived, my dear brothers. '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'Every good gift and every perfect gift is from above, coming down
        from the Father of lights, with whom there is no variation or shadow of change. '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: Doers of the Message, Not Just Hearers'
      title: Doers of the Message, Not Just Hearers
      number: 18
      content: 'By his will he gave birth to us through the message of truth, so
        that we should be a kind of first fruits of his creatures. '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'Understand this, my dear brothers: every person must be quick to
        hear, slow to speak, slow to anger, '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'for human anger does not accomplish the righteousness of God. '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'Therefore, putting aside all moral uncleanness and wicked excess,
        welcome with humility the implanted message which is able to save your souls. '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'But be doers of the message and not hearers only, deceiving yourselves, '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'because if anyone is a hearer of the message and not a doer, this
        one is like someone staring at his own face in a mirror, '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'for he looks at himself and goes away and immediately forgets what
        sort of person he was. '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: 'But the one who looks into the perfect law of liberty and continues
        to do it, not being a forgetful hearer but a doer who acts, this one will
        be blessed in what he does. '
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: "If anyone thinks he is religious, although he does not bridle his
        tongue but deceives his heart, this person\u2019s religion is worthless. "
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: 'Pure and undefiled religion in the sight of our God and Father is
        this: to look after orphans and widows in their affliction, and to keep oneself
        unstained by the world. '
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Partiality Forbidden'
      title: Partiality Forbidden
      number: 1
      content: ' My brothers, do not hold your faith in our glorious Lord Jesus Christ
        with partiality. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'For if someone enters into your assembly in fine clothing with a
        gold ring on his finger, and a poor person in filthy clothing also enters, '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "and you look favorably on the one wearing the fine clothing and you
        say, \u201CBe seated here in a good place,\u201D and to the poor person you
        say, \u201CYou stand or be seated there by my footstool,\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'have you not made distinctions among yourselves and become judges
        with evil thoughts? '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'Listen, my dear brothers! Did not God choose the poor of the world
        to be rich in faith, and heirs of the kingdom that he has promised to those
        who love him? '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'But you have dishonored the poor! Are not the rich exploiting you
        and they themselves dragging you into the courts? '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'Do they themselves not blaspheme the good name of the one to whom
        you belong? '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "However, if you carry out the royal law according to the scripture,
        \u201CYou shall love your neighbor as yourself,\u201D you are doing well. "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'But if you show partiality, you commit sin, and thus are convicted
        by the law as transgressors. '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'For whoever keeps the whole law but stumbles in one point only has
        become guilty of all of it. '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "For the one who said \u201CDo not commit adultery\u201D also said
        \u201CDo not murder.\u201D Now if you do not commit adultery but you do murder,
        you have become a transgressor of the law. "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'Thus speak and thus act as those who are going to be judged by the
        law of liberty. '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: Faith and Works'
      title: Faith and Works
      number: 13
      content: 'For judgment is merciless to the one who has not practiced mercy.
        Mercy triumphs over judgment. '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'What is the benefit, my brothers, if someone says that he has faith
        but does not have works? That faith is not able to save him, is it?  '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'If a brother or a sister is poorly clothed and lacking food for the
        day, '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "and one of you should say to them, \u201CGo in peace, keep warm and
        eat well,\u201D but does not give them what is necessary for the body, what
        is the benefit? "
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'Thus also faith, if it does not have works, is dead by itself. '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "But someone will say, \u201CYou have faith and I have works.\u201D
        Show me your faith apart from your works, and I will show you my faith by
        my works. "
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'You believe that God is one; you do well. Even the demons believe,
        and shudder! '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'But do you want to know, O foolish person, that faith apart from
        works is useless? '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'Was not Abraham our father justified by works when he offered up
        his son Isaac on the altar? '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'You see that faith was working together with his works, and by the
        works the faith was perfected. '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: "And the scripture was fulfilled that says, \u201CAnd Abraham believed
        God, and it was credited to him for righteousness,\u201D and he was called
        God\u2019s friend. "
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'You see that a person is justified by works and not by faith alone. '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: 'And likewise was not Rahab the prostitute also justified by works
        when she welcomed the messengers and sent them out by a different route? '
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: 'For just as the body without the spirit is dead, so also faith without
        works is dead. '
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Restraining the Tongue'
      title: Restraining the Tongue
      number: 1
      content: ' Not many should become teachers, my brothers, because you know that
        we will receive a greater judgment.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'For we all stumble in many ways. If anyone does not stumble in what
        he says, he is a perfect individual, able to hold in check his whole body
        also. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'And if we put bits in the mouths of horses so that they obey us,
        we also guide their whole bodies. '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'Behold also ships: although they are so large and are driven by strong
        winds, they are guided by a very small rudder wherever the inclination of
        the pilot wishes. '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'So also the tongue is a small member of the body and boasts great
        things. Behold how small a fire sets ablaze how great a forest! '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'And the tongue is a fire! The world of unrighteousness, the tongue,
        is set among our members, defiling the whole body and setting on fire the
        course of human existence, being set on fire by hell. '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'For every species of animals and birds, of reptiles and sea creatures,
        is being tamed and has been tamed by the human species, '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'but no human being is able to tame the tongue. It is a restless evil,
        full of deadly poison. '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'With it we bless the Lord and Father, and with it we curse people
        who are made in the likeness of God. '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'From the same mouth come blessing and cursing. My brothers, these
        things ought not to be so! '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'A spring does not pour forth from the same opening fresh and bitter
        water, does it?  '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: The Wisdom That Comes Down from Above'
      title: The Wisdom That Comes Down from Above
      number: 12
      content: 'A fig tree is not able, my brothers, to produce olives, or a grapevine
        figs. Neither can a saltwater spring produce fresh water. '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'Who is wise and understanding among you? Let him show by his good
        behavior his works, with the humility of wisdom. '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'But if you have bitter jealousy and selfish ambition in your hearts,
        do not boast and tell lies against the truth. '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'This is not the wisdom that comes down from above, but is earthly,
        unspiritual, demonic. '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'For where there is jealousy and selfish ambition, there is disorder
        and every evil practice. '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'But the wisdom from above is first pure, then peaceful, gentle, obedient,
        full of mercy and good fruits, nonjudgmental, without hypocrisy, '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'And the fruit of righteousness is sown in peace among those who make
        peace. '
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Subject Yourselves to God'
      title: Subject Yourselves to God
      number: 1
      content: ' From where are conflicts and from where are quarrels among you?
        Is it not from this, from your pleasures that wage war among your members? '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'You desire and do not have; you murder and are filled with envy,
        and are not able to obtain; you fight and quarrel. You do not have because
        you do not ask. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'You ask and do not receive, because you ask with wrong motives, in
        order that you may spend it on your pleasures. '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'Adulterous people! Do you not know that friendship with the world
        is enmity with God? Therefore whoever wants to be a friend of the world makes
        himself an enemy of God. '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "Or do you think that in vain the scripture says, \u201CThe spirit
        which he caused to dwell in us desires jealously\u201D?  "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "But he gives greater grace. Therefore it says, \u201CGod opposes
        the proud, but gives grace to the humble.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'Therefore subject yourselves to God. But resist the devil, and he
        will flee from you. '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'Draw near to God, and he will draw near to you. Cleanse your hands,
        you sinners, and purify your hearts, you double-minded! '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'Lament and mourn and weep! Let your laughter be turned to mourning,
        and your joy to gloominess. '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'Humble yourselves before the Lord, and he will exalt you. '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'Do not speak evil of one another, brothers. The one who speaks evil
        of a brother or judges his brother speaks evil of the law and judges the
        law. But if you judge the law, you are not a doer of the law but a judge
        of the law.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: Arrogant Boasting About the Future'
      title: Arrogant Boasting About the Future
      number: 12
      content: 'There is one lawgiver and judge who is able to save and to destroy.
        But who are you to judge your neighbor? '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "Come now, you who say, \u201CToday or tomorrow we will travel to
        such and such a city and spend a year there, and carry on business and make
        a profit,\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'you who do not know what will happen tomorrow, what your life will
        be like. For you are a smoky vapor that appears for a short time and then
        disappears. '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "Instead you should say, \u201CIf the Lord wills, we will live and
        do this or that.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'But now you boast in your arrogance. All such boasting is evil. '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'Therefore, to the one who knows to do good and does not do it, to
        him it is sin. '
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Woes on the Rich Who Oppress Others'
      title: Woes on the Rich Who Oppress Others
      number: 1
      content: ' Come now, you rich people, weep and cry aloud over the miseries
        that are coming upon you! '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'Your wealth has rotted, and your clothing has become moth-eaten. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'Your gold and silver have become corroded, and their corrosion will
        be a witness against you, and it will consume your flesh like fire. You have
        stored up treasure in the last days. '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'Behold, the wages that were held back by you from the workers who
        reap your fields cry out, and the cries of the reapers have come to the ears
        of the Lord of hosts. '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'You have lived self-indulgently on the earth and have lived luxuriously.
        You have fattened your hearts in the day of slaughter. '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: Exhortation to Patience'
      title: Exhortation to Patience
      number: 6
      content: 'You have condemned, you have murdered the righteous person; he does
        not resist you. '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'Therefore be patient, brothers, until the coming of the Lord. Behold,
        the farmer waits for the precious fruit of the soil, being patient concerning
        it until it receives the early and late rains. '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'You also be patient. Strengthen your hearts, because the coming of
        the Lord is near. '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'Brothers, do not complain against one another, in order that you
        may not be judged. Behold, the judge stands before the doors! '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'Brothers, take as an example of perseverance and endurance the prophets
        who spoke in the name of the Lord. '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'Behold, we consider blessed those who have endured. You have heard
        about the patient endurance of Job, and you saw the outcome from the Lord,
        that the Lord is compassionate and merciful. '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: The Effective Prayer of Faith'
      title: The Effective Prayer of Faith
      number: 12
      content: 'Now above all, my brothers, do not swear either by heaven or by earth
        or by any other oath, but let your yes be yes and your no, no, in order that
        you may not fall under judgment. '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'Is anyone among you suffering misfortune? He should pray. Is anyone
        cheerful? He should sing praise. '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'Is anyone among you sick? He should summon the elders of the church
        and they should pray over him, anointing him with olive oil in the name of
        the Lord. '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'And the prayer of faith will save the one who is sick, and the Lord
        will raise him up, and if he has committed sins he will be forgiven. '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'Therefore confess your sins to one another, and pray for one another,
        so that you may be healed. The effective prayer of a righteous person accomplishes
        much. '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'Elijah was a human being with the same nature as us, and he prayed
        fervently for it not to rain, and it did not rain on the land for three years
        and six months. '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'And he prayed again, and the sky gave rain and the earth produced
        its fruit. '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'My brothers, if anyone among you should wander away from the truth
        and someone turns him back, '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "he should know that the one who turns a sinner back from the error
        of his way will save that person\u2019s soul from death, and will cover over
        a great number of sins. "
      comments: []
